{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#14181: CSS source maps do not work with defineCustomElement and customElement: true",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:15:49.846182+00:00",
  "text": "CSS source maps do not work with defineCustomElement and customElement: true\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.25\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://github.com/Sanderovich/vue-3.5.25-custom-elements-sourcemap\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Checkout the minimal reproduction repository.\n2. Run `npm run dev`.\n3. Inspect the `h1` heading styling.\n\n### What is expected?\n\nI expect an inline source map to be in the inlined `style`-tags, because I enabled source maps in the `vite.config.ts`.\n```\nbuild: {\n    sourcemap: 'inline',\n},\n````\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nThe inlined `style`-tags do not contain source maps.\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
